Definition: New Testament) the sages who visited Jesus and Mary and Joseph shortly after Jesus was born
Example: the Gospel According to Matthew says they were guided by a star and brought gifts of gold and frankincense and myrrh; because there were three gifts it is usually assumed that there were three of them
Synonyms: Magi, collection, i, noun, communication, New_Testament, c, New, Testament, the, sages, who, visited, Jesus, and, Mary, Joseph, shortly, after, was, born, Gospel, According, to, Matthew, says, they, were, guided, by, a, star, brought, gifts, of, gold, frankincense, myrrh, because, there, three, it, is, usually, assumed, that, them
Category: noun.group
